This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   Building the Insight Radar visual layer for ReviewLens AI hackathon demo. The immediate task is extending the `/api/sessions/[id]/insight` endpoint to return an additive `radar` field containing structured theme data (`InsightRadarData`) for use by a recharts spider/radar chart component. This is step 1 of the approved build order from an office hours design session.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - ReviewLens AI: Next.js 14 app router, TypeScript, Postgres, Anthropic Claude SDK, Playwright scrapers
   - Insight Radar: recharts `RadarChart` spider chart on 5-6 theme axes + rotating `QuoteStream`, zero user interaction needed
   - Additive API extension: existing `/insight` response gains a `radar` field; all existing fields unchanged
   - `InsightBrief` cached in `sessions.insight_brief` (JSON text column) — cache must be cleared to test re-generation
   - `generateInsight` in `lib/llm/insight.ts` caps at 200 reviews, `max_tokens=600`, returns structured JSON
   - gstack office hours skill: design doc approved, builder mode (hackathon), target = SaaS founders
   - Caveman mode active (full) — drop articles/filler/pleasantries
   - lat.md knowledge graph — must stay in sync; run `lat check` after code changes
   - MemPalace segfaults (exit 139) on Anaconda Python 3.12 — known issue, use native memory fallback

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`lib/types.ts`** — Defines all shared TypeScript interfaces. Currently has `InsightTheme` and `InsightBrief`. Needs `InsightRadarTheme`, `InsightRadarData` added, and `InsightBrief` extended with `radar?: InsightRadarData`. Full current content:
     ```ts
     export interface InsightTheme {
       title: string;
       description: string;
       quote: string;
     }

     export interface InsightBrief {
       sentiment: string;
       score: number;
       summary: string;
       themes: InsightTheme[];
     }
     ```
     Planned addition:
     ```ts
     export interface InsightRadarTheme {
       name: string;
       score: number;        // 0–100 normalised sentiment score for radar axis
       count: number;        // reviews mentioning this theme
       sentiment: 'positive' | 'negative' | 'mixed';
       topQuote: string;     // verbatim quote ≤100 chars
     }

     export interface InsightRadarData {
       themes: InsightRadarTheme[];
       summary: string;
       ingestedAt: string;
     }

     export interface InsightBrief {
       sentiment: string;
       score: number;
       summary: string;
       themes: InsightTheme[];
       radar?: InsightRadarData;  // NEW — additive, optional for cache compat
     }
     ```

   - **`lib/llm/insight.ts`** — Core LLM function. Current PROMPT outputs 3 themes with title/description/quote. Current `max_tokens=600`. Needs: extend PROMPT to also output a `radar` block with 5-6 themes (name, score 0-100, count, sentiment, topQuote), bump `max_tokens` to ~1200, parse `radar` from response. Full current content:
     ```ts
     import type { Review, InsightBrief } from '@/lib/types';
     import { getClient, MODEL } from './client';

     const PROMPT = `You are a product review analyst. Analyze the provided reviews and return ONLY a JSON object with this exact structure (no markdown fences, no preamble, no trailing text):
     {
       "sentiment": "<positive|mostly positive|mixed|mostly negative|negative>",
       "score": <float 1.0-5.0>,
       "summary": "<one sentence describing overall customer sentiment>",
       "themes": [
         { "title": "<theme name>", "description": "<1-2 sentence description>", "quote": "<exact verbatim substring from a review>" },
         { "title": "<theme name>", "description": "<1-2 sentence description>", "quote": "<exact verbatim substring from a review>" },
         { "title": "<theme name>", "description": "<1-2 sentence description>", "quote": "<exact verbatim substring from a review>" }
       ]
     }
     Rules:
     - themes: exactly 3, ordered by frequency/importance
     - quote: must be a verbatim substring (≤100 chars) from one of the provided reviews
     - score: weighted average of star ratings if available, otherwise 3.0
     - Return raw JSON only — no backticks, no "json" label`;

     function stripFences(raw: string): string {
       return raw.replace(/^```(?:json)?\n?/m, '').replace(/\n?```$/m, '').trim();
     }

     export async function generateInsight(reviews: Review[]): Promise<InsightBrief> {
       const client = getClient();
       const reviewLines = reviews.slice(0, 200).map((r, i) => {
         const rating = r.rating !== null ? `${r.rating}★` : 'unrated';
         return `${i + 1}. (${rating}) ${r.text}`;
       }).join('\n');

       const response = await client.messages.create({
         model: MODEL,
         max_tokens: 600,
         messages: [{ role: 'user', content: `${PROMPT}\n\nREVIEWS:\n${reviewLines}` }],
       });

       const raw = response.content[0].type === 'text' ? response.content[0].text : '';
       return JSON.parse(stripFences(raw)) as InsightBrief;
     }
     ```

   - **`app/api/sessions/[id]/insight/route.ts`** — GET handler. No changes needed to route itself — it stores/returns whatever `generateInsight` returns. The additive `radar` field flows through automatically. Full current content:
     ```ts
     import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
     import { getSession, getAllReviews, getInsightBrief, saveInsightBrief } from '@/lib/db/repo';
     import { generateInsight } from '@/lib/llm/insight';

     export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic';

     export async function GET(
       _req: NextRequest,
       { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }
     ) {
       const { id } = await params;
       const session = await getSession(id);
       if (!session) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Not found' }, { status: 404 });

       const cached = await getInsightBrief(id);
       if (cached) return NextResponse.json(cached);

       const reviews = await getAllReviews(id);
       try {
         const brief = await generateInsight(reviews);
         await saveInsightBrief(id, brief);
         return NextResponse.json(brief);
       } catch (err) {
         const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
         return NextResponse.json({ error: msg }, { status: 500 });
       }
     }
     ```

   - **`lat.md/chat-features.md`** — Knowledge graph section "Proactive Insight Brief" needs updating to document new `radar` field after code changes. Must run `lat check` after.

   - **`CLAUDE.md`** — Skill routing section appended this session. Also contains lat.md instructions: run `lat search` before work, run `lat check` after changes.

